This method first checks if the input list is empty or if its elements are not instances of `PERSON`. If either of these conditions is true, the method returns without writing to the file. Otherwise, it writes the fields of each `PERSON` in the list to the file as specified. Note that you need to cast the generic `T` type to `PERSON` to access its fields. The method uses the `StandardOpenOption.APPEND` option to append the lines to the file.

