    @Override
    default void customize(QuerydslBindings bindings, QDocument root) {

	StringPath[] multiPropertySearchPaths = new StringPath[] {root.prop1, root.prop2, root.prop3};

	/**
	 * Binds prop1, prop2 and prop3 in OR clause
	 * This binding will activate when one of the given properties are searched in query params
	 */
	bindings.bind(multiPropertySearchPaths).all(new MultiValueBinding&lt;StringPath, String&gt;() {
		@Override
		public Predicate bind(StringPath path, Collection&lt;? extends String&gt; values) {
			BooleanBuilder predicate = new BooleanBuilder();
			// Bind paths present in array multiPropertySearchPaths with incoming values
			for (StringPath propertyPath : multiPropertySearchPaths) {
				values.forEach(value -&gt; predicate.or(propertyPath.containsIgnoreCase(value)));
			}
			return predicate;
		}
	});
    }
It will generate sql like:

    select * from document
    where
        lower(document.prop1) like ?1 
        or lower(document.prop2) like ?1 
        or lower(document.prop3) like ?1

Binding the same path multiple times only results in ORs between multiple occurrences of the *same* property, but not between *different* properties.

I propose the following:
```
public Page&lt;Document&gt; find(@QuerydslPredicate(root = Document.class, bindings = OrDslBindings.class) Predicate predicate) {
  return repository.findAll(predicate);
}
```

```
public class OrDslBindings implements QuerydslBinderCustomizer&lt;EntityPath&lt;?&gt;&gt; {

  @Override
  public void customize(QuerydslBindings bindings, EntityPath&lt;?&gt; entityPath) {
    bindings.bind(String.class).all(new MultiValueOrBinding());
  }

  private static class MultiValueOrBinding implements MultiValueBinding&lt;StringPath, String&gt; {

    private boolean first = true;
    private final BooleanBuilder orPredicate = new BooleanBuilder();

    @Override
    public Optional&lt;Predicate&gt; bind(StringPath path, Collection&lt;? extends S&gt; values) {
      values.forEach(value -&gt; orPredicate.or(path.containsIgnoreCase(value)));

      if (first) {
        first = false;
        return Optional.of(orPredicate);
      } else {
        return Optional.empty();
      }
    }
  }
}
```
The binding stores the state and appends each property with OR. It is returned only once, otherwise the framework will duplicate each OR-group and add ANDs between them, which is superfluous.

